Hawk-Eye, Sports Ball-Tracking System, Bought by Sony, FT Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-07T04:56:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/hawk-eye-sports-ball-tracking-system-bought-by-sony-ft-says.html
  Sony Corp. (6758)  said it’s agreed to buy
Hawk-Eye Innovations Ltd., a U.K. company that provides a
computer-based ball-tracking system for tennis and cricket, the
Financial Times reported.  The Japanese company didn’t say how much it paid; analysts
have estimated that it might be worth 20 million pounds ($32
million), the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 